This is your FACE. On a WALL. 
=====================================
Project is hosted at: https://github.com/fahran/facewall
An updated version is hosted at: https://github.com/tomh235/facewall

Instructions for Ubuntu (Linux):

Prequisites:
	Java 1.8 (1.7 also works)
		sudo add-apt-repository ppa:webupd8team/java
		sudo apt-get update
		sudo apt-get install oracle-java8-installer

	Neo4j 1.9.8
		Download tar.gz from: http://info.neotechnology.com/download-thanks.html?edition=community&release=1.9.8&flavour=unix&_ga=1.240594304.2066794311.1414429136
		Untar to a convenient location.
		add to .bashrc: 'export PATH=/neo4jFolderLocation/neo4j-community-1.9.8/bin:$PATH'
		logout and log back in.

	gvm (gradle 1.10)
		curl -s get.gvmtool.net | bash
		gvm install gradle 1.10

	git
		sudo apt-get install git

Setup cmds:
	git clone https://github.com/tcable/facewall.git
	Navigate to project directory.
	gradle startPopDb tomcatRunWar
	open a browser and navigate to http://localhost:9000/facewall

Hurray, your face is now on a wall! Well done....


Meanwhile, somewhere in Redmond.....

Windows instructions:
=======
Follow Instructions to get up and running: 

FOR WINDOWS:

1.	JDK 7 .
a.	Download → http://www.oracle.com/technetwork/java/javase/downloads/jdk7-downloads-1880260.html .
b.	Run .exe file and install appropriate version (32-bit/64-bit) .
c.	Follow through install wizard.

2.	Neo4j .
a.	Download Neo4j 1.9.8 (zip) at http://neo4j.com/download/other-releases/ .
b.	Extract folder to program files.
c.	Open unzipped neo4j-community-1.9.8 folder in program files .
d.	Right click on address bar → copy address as text.
e.	Open control panel → system → advanced system settings.
f.	Open environment variables.
g.	Scroll down system variables and find “path” → double click (edit system variable box appears.) .
h.	Add a “;” to the end of the current variable value → paste the address bar you copied for the location of Neo4j files. 
i.	Make sure at the end of each path before the “;” that “\bin” is written.
j.	Click ok, ok and ok again.
k.  Start menu → cmd → right click and open as administrator.
l.  type "neo4j install". 
m.  After install is complete type "neo4j status"
n.  If "RUNNING" appears then neo4j has been successfully installed.

3.	IntelliJ.
a.	https://www.jetbrains.com/idea/download/ → download intelliJ community edition.
b.	Open and run the .exe file. 
c.	Follow through the setup wizard and install.

4.	GIT.
a.	Download GIT → http://git-scm.com/downloads .
b.	Run .exe file and install.
c.	Follow through the wizard and click option for “Use Git from the Windows Command Prompt".

5.	Java SE Runtime Environment 7.
a.	Ensure you have this version of Java, if not then download it here http://www.oracle.com/technetwork/java/javase/downloads/java-se-jre-7-download-432155.html .
b.	Run .exe file and install using wizard.

6.	Startup. 
a.	Run Neo4j → open as administrator (used powershell, right click and click open as administrator) in command box type “neo4j start”. 
b.	In command prompt, type “cd..” till you push back to just windows.
c.	Then type the path to where you want to run the application from. Eg “cd .\Users\ckang1\Documents\Facewall”.
d.	Once you have accessed this type “git clone https://github.com/tomh235/facewall.git”.
e.	Deploy the application on a local Tomcat server by typing “gradle tomcatRunwar”. 
f.	It can then be accessed on “localhost:9000/facewall”
g.	Open the project in IntelliJ, and run “insertFixturesUltility” to produce the database with the test data. 
